Static Website Hosting on AWS S3  

This project demonstrates how to host a simple static website using **Amazon S3**.  
It is part of my DevOps learning journey as I build hands-on experience with AWS cloud services.  

## 🔹 Project Overview  
- Upload a static website (HTML,Css) to an **S3 bucket**  
- Configure the bucket for **public access**  
- Enable **static website hosting**  
- Test the website by accessing it through the S3 endpoint  

## 🔹 AWS Services Used  
- **Amazon S3** → Stores and serves the static website files  
- **IAM** → For secure access and permissions management  
- **Route 53** → For custom domain mapping  

## 🔹 Outcome  
By the end of this project, I’ll have a **publicly hosted website** on AWS S3 and an understanding of:  
- Static website hosting on AWS  

