  padding: 2rem;
}

footer {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  padding: 1rem;
  background: #222;
  color: white;
}



## 🔹Step-by-Step Deployment on AWS S3

- Create a New S3 Bucket
- Go to AWS S3 console → Click Create bucket
- Bucket name must be globally unique, mystaticwebsite-emem
- Disable “Block all public access”

-Click Create bucket
-Enable Static Website Hosting
-Properties → Static website hosting → Select Use this bucket to host a website
-Set Index document to index.html

Copy the S3 website endpoint → http://mystaticwebsite-emem.s3-website.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com/

Upload Website Files
-Upload index.html and style.css to the root of the bucket
-Set Permissions
-use this bucket policy for public read access

Test the Website
-Open the S3 website endpoint in a browser and my site went live.



